West Bromwich Albion completed the
permanent move of goalkeeper  Ben Foster  from Birmingham, the
Premier League club said on its website.  Foster, who spent last season on loan with the Baggies,
signed a three-year contract with a club option for a further
two seasons. Terms of the transfer werenâ€™t disclosed by either
team.  Foster, 29, started the first 37 games last season, missing
the finale with an injury, in helping West Brom to its best
Premier League finish of 10th place. He tied the club record
with 10 Premier League shutouts.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
